</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A14171E999DE247636816F93EBD9B3C7" pageId="0" pageNumber="173" type="genitalia">
<paragraph id="FDD8A9B88E82B79D3FFE05EA360A5E0F" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">Genitalia.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5ECC9343D68C13893D1754FB5FA04F11" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">
Median lobe of aedeagus curved in lateral view, tip thin and appearing fragile; in ventral view slender and gently narrowed towards tip (Figs 
<figureCitation id="0402C33CAEBDC9AE502B7D9A6F485222" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Liodessus spp. males: Liodessus caxamarca sp. nov., holotype, median lobe of aedeagus in ventral view (A), same in lateral view (B), right paramere external surface view (C); Liodessus altoperuensis sp. nov. holotype, median lobe of aedeagus in ventral view (D), same in lateral view (E), right paramere external surface view (F)." figureDoi="10.3897/alpento.4.55139.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/441854" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">3A, B</figureCitation>
); lateral lobes (parameres) bisegmented and comparably broad (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2FC78841432548274E0AEC7D91EF4CA7" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Liodessus spp. males: Liodessus caxamarca sp. nov., holotype, median lobe of aedeagus in ventral view (A), same in lateral view (B), right paramere external surface view (C); Liodessus altoperuensis sp. nov. holotype, median lobe of aedeagus in ventral view (D), same in lateral view (E), right paramere external surface view (F)." figureDoi="10.3897/alpento.4.55139.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/441854" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">3C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="080C9D615FDD7C0C43419CF3AA6406F9" doi="10.3897/alpento.4.55139.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/441854" pageId="0" pageNumber="173" start="Figure 3" startId="F3">
<paragraph id="56807FD5EFABE9B74E4F07DD22465CE9" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">
<emphasis id="B0FF3628F0C4FB9B5547B3C65D7A7B9C" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">Figure 3.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="C0BECBCD62B47D8F9C624ACA277FC0E0" authorityName="Guignot" authorityYear="1939" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Liodessus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Liodessus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4FD6663A7FE607D66066050193D4BC97" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">Liodessus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. males: 
<taxonomicName id="F0E014FAC295D06453AAA936EF430B63" authorityName="Balke &amp; Megna &amp; Zenteno &amp; Figueroa &amp; Hendrich" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Liodessus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Liodessus caxamarca" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caxamarca">
<emphasis id="DEA7E9A0757C3A33FD2F456962D28F01" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">Liodessus caxamarca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., holotype, median lobe of aedeagus in ventral view (
<emphasis id="6AA480E5A866ECC9FEE00CEB6C4485A9" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">A</emphasis>
), same in lateral view (
<emphasis id="0CFC5435A7C20B5BD6BCA0A9C530B008" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">B</emphasis>
), right paramere external surface view (
<emphasis id="09E051F25B21F53373CB805CD6983704" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">C</emphasis>
); 
<taxonomicName id="60CB00551184DD953CCCD3EE4D382A4B" authorityName="Balke &amp; Megna &amp; Zenteno &amp; Figueroa &amp; Hendrich" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Liodessus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Liodessus altoperuensis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="altoperuensis">
<emphasis id="DEC87EC15F38E3F7C15B23F46EF55699" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">Liodessus altoperuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. holotype, median lobe of aedeagus in ventral view (
<emphasis id="871E932D0EC2C4EE9BDA3A0FBA0CE415" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">D</emphasis>
), same in lateral view (
<emphasis id="7E61FC83BF6A8F5BFA3A1A0778BDDF4D" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">E</emphasis>
), right paramere external surface view (
<emphasis id="3FF0DCDA67380289D4D29B9A000AE30E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">F</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="59B2A4624E09E94091EB7FDAE22F611D" pageId="0" pageNumber="173" type="variation">
<paragraph id="8778C6F98CDE40E64BD333FA4C7089EB" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">Variation.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7E555E51224DB01869AEC0753BB9520A" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">
Total length: 2.5-2.8 mm; length without head: 2.2-2.5 mm; maximum width: 1.1-1.4 mm. The elytral stria can be short yet well visible to very faint to absent. The color is rather variable, from comparably lightly colored (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="91ACDDA73602B569F2771342ABEE8944" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Liodessus spp.: Dorsal habitus of Liodessus caxamarca sp. nov., female paratypes from locality PER _ YSM _ 2018 _ 046 (A), PER _ YSM _ 2018 _ 047 (B), PER _ YSM _ 2018 _ 046 (C), male paratype PER _ YSM _ 2018 _ 046 (D); Liodessus altoperuensis sp. nov., male paratype from locality PER _ YSM _ 2018 _ 050 (E)." figureDoi="10.3897/alpento.4.55139.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/441852" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">1B</figureCitation>
), to more or less dark brown to blackish (Figs 
<figureCitation id="E1695D589B992D167FCAF720455866E0" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Liodessus spp.: Dorsal habitus of Liodessus caxamarca sp. nov., female paratypes from locality PER _ YSM _ 2018 _ 046 (A), PER _ YSM _ 2018 _ 047 (B), PER _ YSM _ 2018 _ 046 (C), male paratype PER _ YSM _ 2018 _ 046 (D); Liodessus altoperuensis sp. nov., male paratype from locality PER _ YSM _ 2018 _ 050 (E)." figureDoi="10.3897/alpento.4.55139.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/441852" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">1A-D</figureCitation>
). Specimens from localities #45 and #46 in 
<normalizedToken id="F95BE1AF29AF62A94331833C6A5FFE73" originalValue="Encañada">Encanada</normalizedToken>
District, Conga are overall darker than from the other localities. This is however not reflected in the haplotype tree we calculated from our 
<emphasis id="6F30B6069D6BFFE7085C8F1C47E215DA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">cox1</emphasis>
data (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="AE8C3C0AD81A28A914441ADFF81B9B1D" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Localities of Liodessus caxamarca sp. nov. sampled for cox 1 data, and haplotype tree inferred using TCS software. Each bar along the lines connecting the 5 haplotypes indicates one inferred nucleotide substitution. The base map was taken from GoogleEarth." figureDoi="10.3897/alpento.4.55139.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/441856" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">5</figureCitation>
). We assessed the length of the metathoracic wings in 10 specimens, which all had the same wing length. This does not rule out the possibility that a certain number of specimens can be fully winged.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E2466D6677EDC0DD4F711D709E22E70F" pageId="0" pageNumber="173" type="female">
<paragraph id="DF874D7B79587095D8F8BD753B0802E5" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">Female.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9D6B7B38A63370A0201A5B15753E11A0" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">
Dorsal surface dull due to presence of well impressed microreticulation between surface punctation (Figs 
<figureCitation id="4E19477CE98449759A16E50CE10E4BAE" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Liodessus spp.: Dorsal habitus of Liodessus caxamarca sp. nov., female paratypes from locality PER _ YSM _ 2018 _ 046 (A), PER _ YSM _ 2018 _ 047 (B), PER _ YSM _ 2018 _ 046 (C), male paratype PER _ YSM _ 2018 _ 046 (D); Liodessus altoperuensis sp. nov., male paratype from locality PER _ YSM _ 2018 _ 050 (E)." figureDoi="10.3897/alpento.4.55139.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/441852" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">1A-C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="9C9732E03BD89C7E1E456B9DB6563382" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Liodessus spp., female paratypes: Metathoracic wing of paratypes of Liodessus caxamarca sp. nov. (A); Liodessus altoperuensis sp. nov. (B)." figureDoi="10.3897/alpento.4.55139.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/441853" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">2A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="10E54335DA9490BA4003CD6438ED00A3" pageId="0" pageNumber="173" type="bold platform">
<paragraph id="8A1A9253B4BEEED3905D1F369566A606" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">BOLD platform.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="34885111F819941A4B9E9D9DB82DE7B7" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">
We provided 27 entries in the 
<normalizedToken id="BCFC1039D666C181A65D3E78E3F04A37" originalValue="“COLLI”">&quot;COLLI&quot;</normalizedToken>
project, all retrieved in one cluster. Assignment to that cluster was unambiguous, meaning all specimens were correctly assigned to this morphologically delineated species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="60283A8B71A8A711991C8B95B11DAB1F" pageId="0" pageNumber="173" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="21D01CFA04DFE36F2DE95F928A170C6B" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B7FCAED3D52066C0D54A05021339CAE9" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">Named after the Caxamarca pre Inca culture that inhabited the area between 200-1,300 AD, and also gave the name to the Department Cajamarca. The name is a noun in the nominative standing in apposition.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="421A5FEDDD50A2151C15C5C90BB04D50" pageId="0" pageNumber="173" type="comparisons">
<paragraph id="77AF37E09997786B1E5CA46D3A5ED65F" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">Comparative notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B2CE1BE1179C1CAF40F88CF57DB48132" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">
The species is well characterized by its size, discontinuous habitus, shape of male genitalia (Figs 
<figureCitation id="CFA107C539D1F58B72F5C7A196814443" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Liodessus spp. males: Liodessus caxamarca sp. nov., holotype, median lobe of aedeagus in ventral view (A), same in lateral view (B), right paramere external surface view (C); Liodessus altoperuensis sp. nov. holotype, median lobe of aedeagus in ventral view (D), same in lateral view (E), right paramere external surface view (F)." figureDoi="10.3897/alpento.4.55139.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/441854" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">3A, B</figureCitation>
) and 
<emphasis id="1908DF013AA1A86B6CDB861275A288FD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">cox1</emphasis>
signature.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B8957BB8848E705C4651388020C6DD40" pageId="0" pageNumber="173" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="E65D8B3FC49910B3A4B6960DD6BAE358" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="636A98A7B47C06ABB78AE85EF7EBEC37" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">
Only known from the high Andes in north western Peru (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9FC85F2E7A90185531D038055C1196F0" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Distribution area (orange dot) of Liodessus caxamarca sp. nov. and Liodessus altoperuensis sp. nov. in the northern Andes of Peru." figureDoi="10.3897/alpento.4.55139.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/441855" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4B771FA7A56D029A71CC6C672A3967CC" pageId="0" pageNumber="173" type="habitat">
<paragraph id="F7B93D41B998D31F12BC4F20FC9B8878" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DC8ED738FFCE6E513668A82015F2CA1A" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">
Shallow and exposed peatland puddles, collected with strainer out of mats of vegetation including mosses (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="CC4C6E55C2C4DCEBEEBF54F2B242915B" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Habitats and landscapes at localities Cajamarca, Cajamarca, Encanada District, Conga, 4030 m [PER _ YSM _ 2018 _ 046] (A, B) and Cajamarca, San Pablo, Tumbaden District, Alto Peru, 3935 m [PER _ YSM _ 2018 _ 51] (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/alpento.4.55139.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/441857" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="5A9B5C893AE9B326EC9C31756CFAEC2B" doi="10.3897/alpento.4.55139.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/441855" pageId="0" pageNumber="173" start="Figure 4" startId="F4">
<paragraph id="DDA5E65473653FAC51C852F509488BA5" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">
<emphasis id="111A5E5B5A4F00D37C4A45E20AD6767C" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">Figure 4.</emphasis>
Distribution area (orange dot) of 
<taxonomicName id="BBA850D25D471AD1E805BE2EF39E468D" authorityName="Balke &amp; Megna &amp; Zenteno &amp; Figueroa &amp; Hendrich" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Liodessus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Liodessus caxamarca" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caxamarca">
<emphasis id="38430379571AB5C80DBC49A13AE1CBB5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">Liodessus caxamarca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. and 
<taxonomicName id="54C368FECDD5ECED80B21544597605F1" authorityName="Balke &amp; Megna &amp; Zenteno &amp; Figueroa &amp; Hendrich" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Liodessus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Liodessus altoperuensis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="altoperuensis">
<emphasis id="FE61FFD6EDAF2EBC0E83AF16CB345B04" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="173">Liodessus altoperuensis</emphasis>
